def apply(self, other):
    if isinstance(other, datetime):
        # convert other to a datetime object
        other = other.replace(tzinfo=None)
        business_offset = self
        n = self.n

        # adjust other to reduce number of cases to handle
        other = business_offset.rollforward(other)

        # get total business hours by sec in one business day
        businesshours = sum(
            business_offset._get_business_hours_by_sec(st, en)
            for st, en in zip(business_offset.start, business_offset.end)
        )

        bd, r = divmod(abs(n * 60), businesshours // 60)
        if n < 0:
            bd, r = -bd, -r

        # adjust by business days first
        if bd != 0:
            other = business_offset.apply_business_day_offset(other, bd, original_bhour_remain=timedelta(), offset=r)

        # remaining business hours to adjust
        other = business_offset.apply_business_hour_offset(other, r, biz_day=bd)

        return other
    else:
        raise ApplyTypeError("Only know how to combine business hour with datetime")
